  "market_context": "On 9 February 2024, Light Crude Oil Futures were trading within a defined intraday range. The London session consolidated without taking either side of the range, setting up a classic NY Manipulation (Power of Three) profile with a bullish bias.",
  "key_observation": "At the 08:30 New York open, price swept below the range low (sell-side liquidity) and then above the range high (buy-side liquidity), creating failure swings on both sides. A Change in State of Delivery (CHoCH) confirmed on the 5-minute chart at the midnight open price, signalling the true bullish move.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified the intraday range by marking the Range High and Range Low on the 15-minute chart.",
    "Step 2: Observed that during the London session price made only a minor high and failed to take out either side of the range, confirming a consolidation / NY Manipulation profile.",
    "Step 3: Dropped to the 5-minute chart and watched the 08:30 New York open, where price swept below the range low (sell-side liquidity sweep) and then swept above the range high, creating failure swings on both sides.",
    "Step 4: Identified a series of down-close candles on the 5-minute chart at the midnight open price level and waited for a close above them to confirm a Change in State of Delivery (CHoCH).",
    "Step 5: Marked the order block (series of down-close candles near the midnight open) and calculated the mean threshold / discount of the range to identify the optimal entry zone.",
    "Step 6: Planned entry at the discount of the range (aligned with the order block mean threshold), with stop-loss placed below the manipulation low, targeting the opposite side of the range (buy-side liquidity / failure swings).",
    "Step 7: Extended the premium/discount range upward to account for the manipulation sweep, confirming the target remained the opposite side of the range; price reached the target after entry was triggered."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price reversed from the discount/order block entry zone after the CHoCH confirmation and delivered to the opposite side of the range (buy-side liquidity / failure swings), reaching the target of approximately 1.75R.",
  "lessons": "When London consolidates without taking either side of a range, expect a NY Manipulation profile at 08:30. Wait for a liquidity sweep on both sides followed by a CHoCH at a key reference level (e.g., midnight open) before entering at discount with a tight stop, targeting the opposite side of the range.",
